{{Politics of Guinea-Bissau}}

The '''Democratic Socialist Party''' ({{lang-pt|Partido Democrático Socialista}}) was a [[political party]] in [[Guinea-Bissau]].

==History==
The party first contested national elections in 2004, when it ran in the [[Guinea-Bissau legislative election, 2004|parliamentary elections]] that year. It received 2% of the vote, but failed to win a seat. In the [[Guinea-Bissau legislative election, 2008|2008 elections]] its vote share fell to 0.4% and it remained without representation in the [[National People's Assembly (Guinea-Bissau)|National People's Assembly]].<ref>[http://africanelections.tripod.com/gw.html Elections in Guinea-Bissau] African Elections Database</ref>

