'''''Keep Left''''' was a pamphlet published in the [[United Kingdom]] in 1947 by the ''[[New Statesman]]'' that was written by [[Michael Foot]], [[Richard Crossman]] and [[Ian Mikardo]]. It advocated a [[Democratic socialism|democratic socialist]] "third force" foreign policy, a socialist Europe acting independently from either the [[United States]] or the [[Soviet Union]], against the pro-American foreign policy of [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]] [[Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs|foreign secretary]] [[Ernest Bevin]]. ''Keep Left'' was a key statement of the Labour left's dissent from the [[1945-51 Labour government]].

