{{Antisemitism}}
'''Renegade Tribune''' is an anti-Semitic, [[white separatist]], [[Holocaust denial|holocaust denying]], historical revisionist<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.splcenter.org/hatewatch/2018/01/02/close-encounters-racist-kind|last1=Zaitchik|first1=Alexander|date=January 2, 2018|title=Close encounters of the racist kind}}</ref>, [[white nationalist]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.local10.com/news/florida/active-neo-nazi-groups-in-florida|date=February 17, 2016|accessdate=August 22, 2018|last1=Torres|first1=Andrea|title=Active neo-Nazi groups in Florida}}</ref>, and [[neo-Nazi]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/blakemontgomery/white-nationalists-internet-radio-advertisers|title=White Nationalists On Internet Radio Are Proving To Be Problematic For Advertisers|last1=Montgomery|first1=Blake|website=Buzzfeed News|date=December 7, 2017|accessdate=August 22, 2018}}</ref> website established in 2012 by Kyle Hunt. The website, which is part of a larger brand known as ''Renegade Broadcasting'', primarily focuses on white separatism and antisemitism<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thepipeline.info/blog/2018/03/30/uk-labour-party-leadership-in-holocaust-denial-fake-history-fail/|title=UK LABOUR PARTY LEADERSHIP IN HOLOCAUST DENIAL FAKE HISTORY FAIL|last1=Brockman|first1=Andy|date=March 30, 2018|accessdate=August 22, 2018|website= The Pipeline}}</ref>. In addition to white separatist and anti-Semitic ideology being posted on the website, it also offers content based on [[Neo-volkisch movements|volkisch paganism]] and harsh criticism of other pagans for "wanting to ruin their bloodlines".
==Labour Party Controversy== In March 2018, Christine Shawcroft, who just became the chairwoman of the Labour Party disputes panel not even three months prior to the event, was found to be defending Alan Bull, a candidate who posted a link to a Renegade Tribune article along with a Facebook post that said, "International Red Cross report confirms the Holocaust of six million Jews is a hoax". As a response to the incident, Renegade Tribune made an article called "UK Labour Candidate Shared Holohoax Article from Renegade Tribune, Suspended by Party".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://blogs.spectator.co.uk/2018/03/labour-cant-tackle-anti-semitism-under-corbyn/|title=Labour can’t tackle anti-Semitism under Corbyn|last1=Daisley|first1=Stephen|date=March 29, 2018|accessdate=August 22, 2018|website=The Spectator}}</ref>
