{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2016}}
{{Use South African English|date=August 2016}}
'''Tony Karon''' is a South African-born journalist and former anti-[[Apartheid]] activist. He is currently [[Al Jazeera America]]'s senior online executive producer.  He was formerly the Senior Editor at [[Time Magazine|Time.com]].<ref name="time-bio">{{cite news|url=http://www.time.com/time/columnist/karon/article/0,9565,494004,00.html |work=Time |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110523102348/http://www.time.com/time/columnist/karon/article/0,9565,494004,00.html |archivedate=23 May 2011 }}</ref>

He is originally from [[Cape Town]], [[South Africa]], and has been living in [[New York City]] since 1993.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://atlanticfreepress.com/home/profiles/userprofile/tonykaron.html|title=Tony Karon|publisher=[[Atlantic Free Press]]|accessdate=3 September 2010}}</ref>

He studied at the [[University of Cape Town]], and in the 1980s, he was a prominent anti-apartheid activist in student movement [[NUSAS]].

He joined TIME in 1997, and has been a Senior Editor since 2000, providing commentary on world affairs.<ref name="time-bio"/> In the past he worked as an activist for the banned [[African National Congress]] in South Africa.

In April 2013, he was hired as a senior online executive producer of the upcoming [[Al Jazeera America]]'s digital team.<ref>http://america.aljazeera.com/update/andrea-stone-and-tony-karon-join-al-jazeera-america</ref>

